Behavioural & social sciences study design

All studies must disclose on these points even when the disclosure is negative.

Study description

The study is a quantitative, and estimates difference-in-differences among a set of matched units.

Research sample

Law enforcement agencies participating in the 1033 program.

Sampling strategy

To prune the sample to comparable agencies, units were matched on a set of pre-treatment covariates. These are described in detail in the methods section of the study. The sample sizes were determined to be sufficient to detect a 0.1 SD increase or decrease in the dependent variables with 80% power, according to the power simulation we detail in the Supplementary Information.

Data collection

All data is publicly available from the Law Enforcement Support Office of the Defense Logistics Agency, and from the FBI crime statistics reporting system.

Timing

The earliest data begin December 2014, and the latest were collected in March of 2020.

Data exclusions

The sample excludes statewise agencies, tribal agencies, and special districts.

Non-participation

There was no non-participation.

Randomization

There was no randomization.

